<div class="tw-foot p"><div class="fn" id="fn5"><p>Abbreviation: RT, radiotherapy.</p></div></div></section></section><section id="sec15"><h3 class="pmc_sec_title">Treatment Characteristics</h3>
<p>Among the entire cohort, 29% of patients underwent radiotherapy alone, 41% underwent surgery plus radiotherapy, and 30% underwent surgery alone. In addition, 18% received chemotherapy. As expected based on standard practice patterns, patients who underwent radiotherapy were more likely to have greater tumor involvement (larger tumors, regionally invasive disease, and positive lymph nodes) and more severe comorbid disease than patients who underwent surgery alone (<a href="#T2" class="usa-link">Table 2</a>).</p>
